CSS2 selectors
E[attr] //selects simple attribute
E[attr=‘value’] //exact way of searching for attributes
E[attr~=‘value’] //searches partial word in attr value
E[attr|=‘value’] //searches for first argument in value

CSS3 selectors
E[attr^=‘value’] //searches beginning string value only
//can be used to apply https protocols, ftp, Mailto 
E[attr$=‘value’] //searches ending string value only
// can be used to apply .doc, .pdf, .svg etc..
E[attr*=‘value’] // searches for any matching string
// We can also chain attribute selectors 
// ex) a[href^=‘http://’][href*=‘folder2/’][href$=‘.pdf’]

E + F {…} // searches adjacent sibling combinator
E ~ F {…} //searches after E 